You drive up to the Ship-wash. There’s no attendant but it looks like there's two options: a regular wash, and for a few more credits you can use that new “turbo-cleaner” feature you’ve been seeing on TV. The boss probably would appreciate the extra polish. 

What’ll it be?

[[Use the turbo-cleaner!|CAUGHT IN WASHER]]

[[He's not worth it, just use the regular|DONT GO IN]]


:: CAUGHT IN WASHER {"position":"325,525","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://lloffert.github.io/pic7_WASHDEATH.png"/>
You power on the turbo-cleaner and put the ship in neutral. The tunnel whirs loudly and dozens of LED lights flash around you as you’re railed along. But as you get closer to the grinding soap bristles and seeing just how fast they’re going, you start to wonder if this hasn’t been properly tested yet. And you’d be right! Both you and your ship are ground to bits in the wash.

You’re not alive, but you are clean.

GAME OVER!



:: COFFEE SHOP {"position":"900,150","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://lloffert.github.io/pic9_COFFEESHOP.png"/>
You pop in to the local coffee chain and place your order with the barista, “Sure, one Xorthop dark roast and one Zeemo coming up!” She pulls a series of levers behind her and tubes of dark goop release into the cups. 

But she put them all on the counter at once, which ones are yours? She disappears into the kitchen before you can ask.

[[Take the drinks on the left |WRONG ORDER]]

[[take the drinks on the right |RIGHT ORDER]]


